  <p>Our model (shown above) suggests that there are three main areas we need to explore: </p><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p>The impact of ecosystem strategy on <strong>traditional strategy</strong></p></li><li><p>The impact of ecosystem strategy on <a href="http://www.marketingjournal.org/the-innovation-ecosystem-new-rules-for-the-future-christian-sarkar-and-philip-kotler/" target="_blank"><strong>innovation</strong></a></p></li><li><p>The impact of ecosystem strategy on <a href="http://www.marketingjournal.org/ecosystem-marketing-the-future-of-competition-christian-sarkar-and-philip-kotler/" target="_blank"><strong>marketing</strong></a></p></li></ol><p>Central to all three is not only the <strong>customer</strong>, but also the market, and society itself. </p><p>Our destiny as a species, as individuals, and as businesses now depends on understanding and nurturing the <strong>common good </strong>across the natural and unnatural walls and boundaries we have built for ourselves.</p><p>Stay tuned for more.</p>]]></description></item><item><title>The Kotler Collection at the John and Mable Ringling Museum of Art, Sarasota, Florida</title><dc:creator>Philip Kotler</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 25 Jan 2019 05:47:49 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pkotler.org/blog/2019/1/25/the-kotler-collection-at-the-john-and-mable-ringling-museum-of-art-sarasota-florida</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5b70ba0755b02c6b273319ec:5b70d654cd83663481cdf40a:5c4a9f5542bfc1298b9b85ae</guid><description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://emuseum.ringling.org/emuseum/exhibitions/607"><strong>The Philip and Nancy Kotler Glass Collection</strong></a> is comprised of works by many of the leading glass artists in the American and European traditions, and includes works by Nicolas Africano, Silvia Levenson, Peter Hora, and Stanislav Libensky among many others. Nancy and I donated our Studio Glass collection to <a href="https://www.ringling.org/"><strong>The Ringling</strong></a> in 2012 to share our love for Studio Glass with the public. </p>


































































  

    
  
    

      

      
