ink>https://www.pkotler.org/blog/2019/1/24/a-list-of-kotler-related-websites</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5b70ba0755b02c6b273319ec:5b70d654cd83663481cdf40a:5c49fe41562fa72365a0c308</guid><description><![CDATA[<p class="">Some of you have asked me for more information on the various websites that I participate in and public in regularly, so I’ve made a list:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.pkotler.org"><strong>PKotler.org</strong></a> - this is my main site with information about my books and biography</p></li><li><p class="">My official <a href="https://twitter.com/kotl"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/Philip-Kotler-225204860825666/"><strong>Facebook</strong></a> accounts</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="http://fixcapitalism.com"><strong>FIXCapitalism.com</strong></a> - my work related to my book <em>Confronting Capitalism</em></p></li><li><p class=""><a href="http://www.democracyindecline.com"><strong>DemocracyinDecline.com</strong></a> - my work related to my book <em>Democracy in Decline</em></p></li><li><p class=""><a href="http://www.activistbrands.com"><strong>ActivistBrands.com</strong></a> - my work related to <em>Brand Activism</em> (in collaboration with Christian Sarkar)</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="http://www.marketingjournal.org"><strong>The Marketing Journal</strong></a> - insights into the future of marketing (we also have a <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/groups/13616050/"><strong>LinkedIn Group</strong></a>)</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://regenmarketing.org"><strong>The Regenerative Marketing Institute</strong></a> - promoting regeneration (co-founded with Christian Sarkar and Enrico Foglia)</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.regenerationjournal.org"><strong>The Regeneration Journal</strong></a> - our publication from the Institute</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Sarasotainstitute.global</strong> - articles written or selected by the think tank The Sarasota Institute (TSI)</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="http://www.philkotler.com"><strong>PhilKotler.com</strong></a> - a secondary site about my work</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.worldmarketingsummitgroup.org"><strong>World Marketing Summit</strong></a> - an independent global organization that promotes an annual marketing summit, seminars, research, an annual journal, and academic courses and programs</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.kotlerimpact.com"><strong>Kotler Impact</strong></a> - the marketing &amp; sales Partner of The World Marketing Summit</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.kotlerawards.com"><strong>Kotler Awards</strong></a> - developed to honor true mastery in the field of marketing and management, and to celebrate the achievements of advertising and marketing teams and individuals alike</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://kotlermarketing.com"><strong>Kotler Marketing Group</strong></a> - the work I do with my brother, Milton Kotler</p></li><li><p class=""><strong>Medium (publications)</strong> - 9 or more of my short articles are published by Medium.</p></li></ul>]]></description></item><item><title>The first Philip Kotler Presidential Award</title><dc:creator>Philip Kotler</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 17 Jan 2019 21:25:40 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.pkotler.org/blog/2019/1/17/the-philip-kotler-presidential-award-2019</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5b70ba0755b02c6b273319ec:5b70d654cd83663481cdf40a:5c40c8f5cd83668ca5931550</guid><description><![CDATA[<p>The&nbsp;<a href="https://www.worldmarketingsummitgroup.org" target="_blank"><strong>World Marketing Summit</strong></a><strong> (WMS)</strong> just presented India’s Prime Minister&nbsp;Narendra Modi&nbsp;with the first&nbsp;Philip Kotler Presidential Leadership Award.&nbsp; The concept underlying the award is to honor a major public leader who has given new life to democracy and economic growth in that nation.&nbsp;</p><p>Here is a letter I sent the Prim